parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the SRS unit can cause the airbag warning light to illuminate, and in some cases, may lead to airbag deployment failures, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates on the instrument panel
the airbag system may not deploy properly in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing the Takata airbag recall can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident, as the faulty airbag may deploy improperly or not deploy at all.
symptoms: The airbag warning light may illuminate
the vehicle may be inoperable
the owner may experience delays in receiving a repair or replacement airbag.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Repair and Loaner Vehicle Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate repair and loaner vehicle issues can cause inconvenience, additional expenses, and potential safety risks to the vehicle owner.
symptoms: The owner may experience delays in receiving a repair or replacement airbag
may be provided with a loaner vehicle that is not comparable to their own vehicle
may incur additional fuel costs
and may experience inconvenience and frustration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the axle due to rust can cause loss of acceleration, loss of control, and increase the risk of accidents, especially when occurring on a busy highway.
symptoms: Sudden loss of acceleration
dull thud sound
inability to move the vehicle
vehicle becomes disabled on the road.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manufacturer to include certain models in the recall, despite meeting all other criteria, can leave vehicles vulnerable to safety risks and put drivers and passengers at risk.
symptoms: Vehicle not included in recall despite meeting all other criteria
lack of notification from manufacturer
increased risk of accidents due to faulty components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent no-start condition can leave the driver stranded, causing inconvenience and potentially putting them in a dangerous situation. It can also lead to additional costs for towing and repair.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to start after being parked for a period of time
requiring a jumpstart to get it running again. The issue occurs intermittently
with no clear pattern.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The battery drain or parasitic drain can cause the vehicle to not start, leading to inconvenience and potentially putting the driver in a dangerous situation. It can also lead to additional costs for battery replacement and repair.
symptoms: The vehicle's battery is drained
even when the vehicle is turned off
causing the vehicle to not start. The issue may be intermittent
making it difficult to diagnose.
